    "The table state and the planning history are then updated by.",
    "Complex task decompositionInspired by the CoT and [84] prompting methods, researchers instruct LLMs to decompose complex table tasks into simpler sub-tasks.",
    "DIN-SQL [85] proposes breaking down the NL2SQL task into subtasks.",
    "The process involves identifying the relevant tables and columns associated with the query and producing intermediate subqueries.",
    "DEA-SQL [86] and TabSQLify [87] also follow the principle of decomposing tables into smaller, simplifying subtasks and reducing irrelevant information."
